## From https://jasonstitt.com/gitignore-whitelisting-patterns

# 1. Ignore everything
*

# 2. But descend into directories
!*/

# 3. Allow specific files and file extensions
!.gitignore
!*.md
!*.tf
!*.yaml
!*.yml
!*.ico
!*.svg
!*.css
!*.css.map
!*.js
!*.js.map
!*.html
!*.txt
!*.json
!*.png
!*.jpg
!*.jpeg
!*.gif
!*.webp

# Next.js specific files
!*.ts
!*.tsx
!*.jsx
!*.mjs
!*.cjs
!next.config.*
!.eslintrc.*
!.prettierrc.*
!.env.example
!tsconfig.json
!package.json
!package-lock.json
!yarn.lock
!.nvmrc

# 4. Block specific directories and files
*.git
**/.terraform*
**/*env
**/TMP
.next/
node_modules/
.vercel/
.env*.local
*.log
.DS_Store
coverage/
.turbo
build/
dist/
out/
